07/08/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Two grenades were fired at the building housing the Macedonian government early Monday (August 6th) causing slight damage but no injuries. 
Government spokesman Ivica Bocevski said the grenades were fired from about 400m away and landed 100m short of the building. 
Both grenades were manufactured in South Africa, he added. 
Bocevski described the incident as a "terrorist attack" but did not elaborate. 
Security has been tightened at government offices around the country. 
(Xinhua, MIA, Vecer - 07/08/07; DPA, Reuters, Makfax, AFP, DPA, Xinhua- 06/08/07)
